    <!-- Policies Screen -->
    <string name="policies">Policies</string>

    <!-- General -->
    <string name="policies_title">Use Policy and Referral Program</string>
    <string name="policies_intro">
        This application offers a referral program based exclusively on real and verifiable purchases of products or services provided by companies registered on the platform.
    </string>

    <!-- Section 1 -->
    <string name="policies_section_1_title">1. How the referral program works</string>
    <string name="policies_section_1_body">
        Monetary rewards are generated only when a referred user effectively purchases a product or service available in the application. No payments are made for simply registering referrals or for the number of invited users. Registering referrals does not guarantee income.
    </string>

    <string name="policies_section_1_example">
        Example: A user may have multiple registered referrals; however, if none of them purchase a product or service offered by an affiliated company, no payment will be generated.
    </string>

    <!-- Section 2 -->
    <string name="policies_section_2_title">2. Not a pyramid scheme</string>
    <string name="policies_section_2_body">
        This application is not a pyramid, multi-level, or investment scheme. No guaranteed income is promised. Earnings depend exclusively on real commercial transactions and not on the growth of a user network. No payments or investments are required to participate.
    </string>

    <!-- Section 3 -->
    <string name="policies_section_3_title">3. Verification and control</string>
    <string name="policies_section_3_body"> Rewards offered through the referral program may be subject to review by the corresponding service provider or financial institution. Payments are processed through the Ecuadorian financial system by the appropriate financial institutions. This application does not process, manage, or intervene in payment transactions and does not have control over the payment processing
        systems. The platform may limit or disable access to the referral program in cases of suspected fraudulent, abusive, or improper use.
    </string>

    <!-- Section 4 -->
    <string name="policies_section_4_title">4. Payment information</string>
    <string name="policies_section_4_body">
        To receive payments, the user must provide a valid bank account in their own name. The user is solely responsible for ensuring that the provided personal and banking information is accurate, complete, and up to date.
    </string>

    <!-- Section 5 -->
    <string name="policies_section_5_title">5. User responsibility</string>
    <string name="policies_section_5_body">
        The platform is not responsible for failed payments, delays, or losses related to payment processing. Payments, if applicable, are handled by the Ecuadorian financial system and the corresponding financial institutions. This application does not process or manage payment transactions. Users are responsible for
        providing accurate and truthful information. Use of the application implies acceptance of these policies.
    </string>

